          <h3 class="base-aside-card__title font-sans text-md font-bold text-color-text relative">
            
<!---->          </h3>

<!---->
            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          Here are the highest-paying companies in the UK for Software Engineers!

(based on 'all levels' from Levels.fyi):

🥇 Citadel – £274,692
🥈 Wintermute – £274,382
🥉 Meta – £242,189

I posted late last year about how US companies (especially HFT / quant firms) were dominating UK compensation. Back then, Wintermute (UK founded) weren’t even in the top 10.

Now they’ve jumped to #2, ahead of HRT, Jane Street, Meta and other huge names.

Every company in the top 10 is now averaging £200K+ total comp for engineering roles. That would have been unthinkable for London just a few years ago.

For founders: if you want to attract top engineering talent, this is your benchmark.

As an aside, if you compare the London top 10 with the San Francisco top 10 you see a completely different type of company. 

SF is tech dominated. UK is still very much finance dominated. 

I'd love to see more UK founded tech companies in this top list!
        
            </p>

