          💰 Software Developer Salaries in Wales – Aug 2025 Snapshot 💰 

Thinking of hiring or making a move in tech? Here's a breakdown of what Software Developers and Engineers are earning across Wales right now:

Interestingly, The Median Salary for Software Developers in Wales is £42,473 per year, showing a 5.88% increase from 2024, but compared to the national average Wales is still 13% below this!

Salary Ranges based off major hiring spots in Wales are reported to be:

Junior/Graduate level Software Developers - £28,000 – £35,000
Mid-Level Software Developers: £42,000 – £50,000
Senior Software Developers: £55,000 – £65,000+
Lead Software Developers: £65,000 - £80,000 

Regional Highlights

Wrexham: £53,933
Cardiff: £45,830
Swansea: £43,183
Newport: £37,730

Salaries are rising steadily, especially in Fintech, AI, and cybersecurity. With the increase in digital transformation and cloud migration in multiple public sector organisations this could also be the reason for an increase in Software Development resources.

We are also finding that Hybrid and Remote roles are pushing compensation higher in competitive regions to compete with other areas of the UK.

Whether you're benchmarking for hiring or planning your next move, drop me a DM for a more detailed 2025 Salary Bench-marking document 🙌.

#recruitment #salaries #technology

*Information is based off 153 adverts/salaries reported around 18th August 2025.
        
            </p>

