            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          If you're a Golang Engineer looking for work but struggling to get traction, it could be the most basic thing that's getting in your way 👀


Put "Golang" in your profile instead of "Go".

Put yourself in the shoes of a recruiter or hiring manager.

If we search for "Go" on profiles, we find things like

"In my spare time, I like to go hiking"

"I worked in a go to market team"

It's almost impossible to know that you use Golang unless you explicitly state so or if we know for sure that your business uses it. 

Maybe it's worth a try?
        
            </p>

