<!---->
      
<!---->
        <div class="base-aside-card__info self-center pl-1 flex flex-col flex-1">
          <h3 class="base-aside-card__title font-sans text-md font-bold text-color-text relative">
            
<!---->          </h3>

<!---->
            <p class="base-aside-card__subtitle font-sans text-sm text-color-text leading-regular break-words overflow-anywhere
                line-clamp-2">
              
          I’m getting more questions around inside vs outside IR35 rate cards across AI &amp; Data roles, so here’s a grounded view of what’s landing across the M4 corridor.

This is based on live conversations with contractors and hiring managers.

AI Architect designs and oversees the strategic implementation of AI across the organisation.

Outside IR35: £750–£900/day | Inside IR35: £850–£1,000/day

What drives rates: enterprise scale, ownership of AI strategy, governance, stakeholder influence, and accountability beyond delivery.

Machine Learning Engineer designs, builds, deploys and maintains ML systems in production.

Outside IR35: £550–£700/day | Inside IR35: £650–£800/day

What drives rates: production ML experience, real pipelines, reliability, and impact beyond notebooks.

MLOps Engineer builds and runs platforms that deploy, monitor and manage ML models in production.

Outside IR35: £600–£750/day | Inside IR35: £700–£850/day

What drives rates: ownership of the full model lifecycle, platform stability, incident response, and ability to operate at scale.

Data Scientist applies statistics, engineering and domain knowledge to solve business problems.

Outside IR35: £450–£600/day | Inside IR35: £550–£700/day

What drives rates: commercial outcomes, stakeholder communication, and influence on decision-making, not just modelling.

A few market realities worth calling out.
For contractors, the decision between inside and outside IR35 usually comes down to overall take-home, contract length, and how clearly defined the work is, not just the headline day rate.

For hiring managers, getting the IR35 determination right upfront is key. When this is done accurately, especially with an agency that has a clear IR35 assessment process in place, it reduces risk, avoids rework, and often leads to better quality contractors and stronger value for money.

If useful, I’m happy to share how teams are structuring roles to attract strong talent without overpaying.

#IR35
#AIJobs
#DataCareers
#ContractorsUK
#HiringManagers

        
            </p>

